[placement_rules] Roads do NOT conduct power. Only wires, zone tiles, and road+wire crossings conduct. When a road separates zones from a plant, build a wire across the road.
[placement_rules] Zones propagate power to adjacent zones for free. Chain zones together (touching) to avoid unnecessary wire placement.
[placement_rules] find_empty_area can return false positives near water or existing structures. Always verify with inspect_area before committing funds.
[placement_rules] When a 3x3 zone placement is rejected on a clear-looking spot, shift 1-2 tiles and retry rather than insisting on the same coordinates.
[placement_rules] Building road or wire through a 3x3 zone footprint blocks zone placement. Keep infrastructure adjacent to, not inside, the footprint.
[placement_rules] get_infrastructure station counts can be unreliable. Use inspect_area to verify actual buildings on the map.
[strategy] Three-Ring layout is optimal: industrial at map edges (pollution spills off), commercial as buffer, residential in center (highest land value).
[strategy] Two-zone strip pattern (two rows of zones with one road between) is 25% denser than donut layout with 48% less road infrastructure.
[strategy] Each zone needs only ONE tile of road touching it. The game does not require connected road networks.
[strategy] After 2-3 turns of flat/negative reward in the same area, pivot to a new clean area or different growth lever instead of repeating.
[strategy] Fixing infrastructure (power/road) in dense existing neighborhoods produces stronger reward than gambling on new zones in unproven areas.
[strategy] Nuclear power ($5k, 2000 units) is far superior to coal ($3k, 700 units): 2.86x power/dollar, zero pollution.
[tools] query_zone power flags can be delayed/noisy. Zone growth can occur even when query reports unpowered. Don't overreact with more plants.
[bugs] get_infrastructure can report zero police/fire stations while inspect_area shows them. Treat station counts as unreliable.
[strategy] When both job valves are maxed but residential stalls, a single cheap commercial zone in a proven corridor is a strong recovery move.
[2026-04-01 23:29:07] [strategy] When a new police station is built, immediately check budget funding; an unfunded station gives zero police effect and can tank score despite the placement cost.
[2026-04-01 23:29:46] [placement_rules] If a zone remains unpowered across a road, place the wire directly on the road tile to create a road+wire crossing; adjacent parallel wire is not enough.
